# Staff UI and Student PDF

- Show Writing Feedback after Documents only for enabled courses.
- Desktop uses queue/detail split view; smaller viewports use one panel with an explicit back action.
- Preserve visible focus, semantic labels, keyboard operation, and existing instructor-shell behavior.
- Reuse the exact EngE-AI variables `--color-chbe-green`, `--color-ubc-blue`, `--color-navy-blue`, `--background-2`, `--border-color`, `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--hover-bg`, `--sidebar-bg`, and `--chat-bg`; do not create near-duplicate token names.
- Keep the task-first action order: Import from Canvas, Upload files, Add text, then Edit rubric (or read-only View rubric for TAs).
- Use inline import/rubric panels with loading, empty, not-configured/demo, error/retry, dirty, saved-draft, approved-version, preview, and released states. Do not use browser alerts/confirms for normal workflow.
- Use existing toast patterns only as a supplement to durable inline state. Add suitable live-region semantics and never expose raw errors or student text.
- At 900px and below, only the active queue/detail panel may remain visible/focusable; preserve filter/scroll/focus context on Back to submissions.
- Use text plus color for statuses, `:focus-visible`, 44px touch targets, and `prefers-reduced-motion`; never use `transition: all`.
- Clearly separate extracted/verified student text, model draft, staff revision, approval, and release.
- Show approved rubric version separately from unsaved/saved draft state; saving never implies approval, and approval never implies Canvas synchronization.
- Destructive or external actions require explicit confirmation; generation is not release.
- Student PDFs contain approved levels/grade, strengths, evidence, revision priorities, and next goals.
- PDFs exclude confidence, internal flags, model/prompt metadata, and staff-only notes.
